 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Chief Data and Analytics Officer MGM Resorts International 2,102 reviews Las Vegas, NV Full-time MGM Resorts International 2,102 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Location: 
Las Vegas, Nevada 
Become one of the stars behind The SHOW and become part of the world’s most powerful entertainment brands. Our Company has one exciting mission:  To entertain the human race. 
PRIMARY PURPOSE: 
The Chief Data and Analytics Officer plays a critical role in the strategic evolution of MGM Resorts International. This role will be responsible for accelerating the usage of data as a strategic asset to achieve commercial, operational and experiential excellence across the entire company and open the doors for new business ideas and new customer demographics. This role oversees three primary functions: data science, data management & engineering, and advanced analytics & business intelligence. Acting as a shared service across all the business COEs in the company, the CDAO will advocate and enable a data-driven decision culture. This role will directly report to the Chief Strategy, Innovation, and Technology Officer of the company. 
PRINCIPAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES: 
Partner with all lines of business in the company to provide advanced analytic data modeling systems. 
Design and launch innovative and complex analytic models, utilizing a blend of contemporary and traditional data science techniques, across both structured and unstructured data sets. 
Lead a range of data-related functions that include data management and governance, data integrity and validation, and an enterprise-wide data strategy. 
Establish a core competency in producing advanced analytics – both for real-time as well as strategic decision support. 
Oversee the creation of a consolidated set of business intelligence tools and self-service tools to enable end-user-driven analytics: reporting, visualization, and others. 
Oversee data and analytics reporting for key management and board presentations. 
SUPERVISION: 
VP of Engineering and Data Platforms 
VP of Operations Analytics and Data Science 
MINIMUM REQUIREMENTS: 
Masters Degree in data science or equivalent 
4+ years of experience leading a robust data and analytics function in a complex business 
10+ years of hands-on experience in the data and analytics space 
Proven experience in utilizing open source and third-party AI/ML platforms and solutions as well as internally developed advanced data science modeling 
PREFERRED:
 Relevant experience in the hospitality, travel, and entertainment industries 
CERTIFICATIONS, LICENSES, REGISTRATIONS: 
Proof of eligibility to work in the US. 
Gaming registration(s) as required by regional jurisdiction(s) 
KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, AND ABILITIES: 
Demonstrable ability to recruit, retain and mentor high-performance talent in the data science, engineering, and analytics areas 
Hands-on knowledge of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning, utilizing external platforms as well as creating internal capabilities 
Deep understanding of contemporary and traditional data science techniques, across both structured and unstructured data sets 
Proven expertise in creating robust enterprise-wide data infrastructure and data operations 
Strong communication and collaboration skills, and ability to work across diverse business and technology groups 
Experience leading large, cross-functional teams to complete major projects with aggressive timelines and performance metrics balancing near term results and long-term goals 
Proven experience presenting to, collaborating with, and influencing senior executives 
